The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Car thief flees hospital
                                                                                                               Car thief flees hospital
                            
	Bolpur, June 15: A youth allegedly caught stealing a motorbike yesterday hit a guard today and fled the hospital where he had been admitted after a mobs thrashing.        
	Shankar Rakshit, 22, fled the Rampurhat Subdivisional Hospital around 7am after unlocking his room with the key snatched from the guard. When a nurse went to dress his wounds, she found the home-guard lying unconscious, said a police officer. A hunt has begun for Shankar.        
	Home-guard Kali Chatterjee has had to be hospitalised with a bruised head.                                                                                                                                                                             
